HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 504
By Hurt
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Isha Wade on her
receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Isha Wade of Gibson County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of her laudable commitment to
her community; and
WHEREAS, a devoted volunteer, Isha Wade is the founder of The Neighborhood Closet,
an endeavor that provides clothes, shoes, and school supplies to children in need; additionally,
she volunteers with TN SHIP, CASA of the Midwest for Gibson County Juvenile Court, Hospice,
RIFA, Community Kitchen, and the Gibson County Christian Women's Job Corp; and
WHEREAS, showing love through action while teaching her children the value of selfless
service, Ms. Wade mentors women entering transitional homes, coaches youth basketball, and
teaches Bible study at her church; and
WHEREAS, Isha Wade aims to leave a lasting legacy of love and compassion for her
community; and
